==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Induction generator
<hw>In*duc"tion gen"er*a`tor</hw>. <def>A machine built as an induction
motor and driven above synchronous speed, thus acting as an
alternating-current generator; -- called also <altname>asynchronous
generator</altname>. Below synchronism the machine takes in electrical
energy and acts as an induction motor; at synchronism the power
component of current becomes zero and changes sign, so that above
synchronism the machine (driven for this purpose by mechanical power)
gives out electrical energy as a generator.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Induction motor</ent>⟦br⟧
